My only resistance to "out now" is the same as it was in Vietnam: the physical impossibility. It took several months to lay the groundwork for the invasion; it will take time to get everybody out, even assuming a deliberate policy of doing it ASAP.

"Set the date!" was the alternate slogan then and it's the one I push now. (And "the date" is more like "the end of the year," not "when the job is done" or any of that crap.)

So I say STDD&amp;GTHO: Set The Damn Date &amp; Get The Hell Out.
